{
  "url": "https://www.w3schools.com/html/html_table_headers.asp",
  "title": "HTML ",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "HTML Table Headers"
    },
    {
      "type": "other",
      "text": "❮ Previous\nNext ❯"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "HTML tables can have headers for each column or row, or for many columns/rows."
    },
    {
      "type": "other",
      "text": "EMIL\nTOBIAS\nLINUS\n\n\n \n \n \n\n\n \n \n \n\n\n \n \n \n\n\n \n \n \n\n\n \n \n \n\n\n\n\n8:00\n \n \n\n\n9:00\n \n \n\n\n10:00\n \n \n\n\n11:00\n \n \n\n\n12:00\n \n \n\n\n13:00\n \n \n\n\n\n\n\nMON\nTUE\nWED\nTHU\nFRI\n\n\n8:00\n \n \n \n \n \n\n\n9:00\n \n \n \n \n \n\n\n10:00\n \n \n \n \n \n\n\n11:00\n \n \n \n \n \n\n\n12:00\n \n \n \n \n \n\n\n\n\nDECEMBER"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "HTML Table Headers"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Table headers are defined with th elements. \nEach th element represents a table cell."
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "html",
          "code": "<table>  <tr>    <th>Firstname</th>    \n  <th>Lastname</th>    <th>Age</th>  </tr>  \n  <tr>    <td>Jill</td>    <td>Smith</td>    \n  <td>50</td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td>Eve</td>    \n  <td>Jackson</td>    <td>94</td>  </tr></table>"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Vertical Table Headers"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "To use the first column as table headers, define the first cell in each row as a \n<th> element:"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "html",
          "code": "<table>  <tr>    <th>Firstname</th>    \n  <td>Jill</td>    <td>Eve</td>  </tr>  \n  <tr>    \n  <th>Lastname</th>    <td>Smith</td>    \n  <td>Jackson</td>  </tr>  <tr>    <th>Age</th>    <td>94</td>    \n  <td>50</td>  </tr></table>"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Align Table Headers"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "By default, table headers are bold and centered:"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": [
        [
          "Firstname",
          "Lastname",
          "Age"
        ],
        [
          "Jill",
          "Smith",
          "50"
        ],
        [
          "Eve",
          "Jackson",
          "94"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "To left-align the table headers, use the CSS text-align property:"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "css",
          "code": "th {  text-align: left;\n}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Header for Multiple Columns"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "You can have a header that spans over two or more columns."
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": [
        [
          "Name",
          "Age"
        ],
        [
          "Jill",
          "Smith",
          "50"
        ],
        [
          "Eve",
          "Jackson",
          "94"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "To do this, use the colspan attribute on the \n<th> element:"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "html",
          "code": "<table>  <tr>    <th colspan=\"2\">Name</th>    <th>Age</th>  </tr>  \n  <tr>    <td>Jill</td>    <td>Smith</td>    \n  <td>50</td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td>Eve</td>    \n  <td>Jackson</td>    <td>94</td>  </tr></table>"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "other",
      "text": "You will learn more about colspan and rowspan in the Table colspan & rowspan chapter."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Table Caption"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "You can add a caption that serves as a heading for the entire table."
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": [
        [
          "Month",
          "Savings"
        ],
        [
          "January",
          "$100"
        ],
        [
          "February",
          "$50"
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "To add a caption to a table, use the <caption> tag:"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "html",
          "code": "<table style=\"width:100%\">  <caption>Monthly savings</caption>  <tr>    <th>Month</th>    <th>Savings</th>  </tr>  <tr>    <td>January</td>    <td>$100</td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td>February</td>    <td>$50</td>  </tr>\n </table>"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "other",
      "text": "Note: The <caption> tag \nshould be inserted immediately after the <table> tag."
    },
    {
      "type": "other",
      "text": "❮ Previous\nNext ❯"
